<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>CATTSS user study alpha</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />

<link href="main.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />
<script>
    function onload() {
        var w = window,
        d = document,
        e = d.documentElement,
        g = d.getElementsByTagName('body')[0],
        x = w.innerWidth || e.clientWidth || g.clientWidth,
        y = w.innerHeight|| e.clientHeight|| g.clientHeight;
        document.getElementById('width').value=x;
        document.getElementById('height').value=y;
        
        document.getElementById('device').value=navigator.userAgent+'';
    }
</script>
</head>
<body onload="onload()">
<div class="container">
    <div id="title"><h1>Feedback</h1></div>
    <p>Thank you for participating in this study, please provide some feedback:</p>
    <form action="/feedback" method="post" autocomplete="on">
        <input type="text" name="userid" value="<%= userid %>" hidden>
        <input id='width' type="text" name="screenwidth" value="" hidden>
        <input id='height' type="text" name="screeneheight" value="" hidden>
        <input id='device' type="text" name="userAgent" value="" hidden>
        Which version of the app did you prefer?:<br>
        <input class="radioBig" type="radio" name="preference" value="<%= userid%2 %>" > the first one <br>
        <input class="radioBig" type="radio" name="preference" value="<%= (1+userid)%2 %>"> the second one<br>
        <br>
        What best describes the device you are using?:<br>
        <input class="radioBig" type="radio" name="device" value="phone" > smartphone <br>
        <input class="radioBig" type="radio" name="device" value="tablet"> tablet <br>
        <input class="radioBig" type="radio" name="device" value="desktop"> desktop <br>
        <input class="radioBig" type="radio" name="device" value="other"> other <br>
        <br>
        What did you like, dislike, find confusing, find annoying, enjoy, etc. about either of the versions?
        <textarea class="feedbacktext" name="response"></textarea>
        <br>
        If you would be willing to participate in a later study, please provide your email address:<br>
        <input class="feedbacktext" type="email" name="email" value=""><br>
        <br>
        <input class='button' type="submit" value="Submit">
    </form>
    
</div>
</body>
</html>
